data.title: Who's on the Wall
data.meta_description: Nearly 100 University of Minnesota faculty and alumni are featured on the Discovery Wall, which includes Dr. Robert Good’s notes for an article on the first successful bone transplant, James Ryan’s patent drawings of the airplane flight recorder, Dr. Catherine Verfaille’s notes on the stem cell research, and even Bob Dylan’s lyrics to “Temporary Like Achilles.” The installation allows viewers a window into the minds of the University’s most renowned faculty and students.
